competition at the 2024 Olympics began Aug. 1 and will end Aug. 11.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The track and field competition\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2440}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did You Know:There also is an annual Paris Marathon, which first was held in 1976, but it does not follow the same route the runners will experience during the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2667, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an annual Paris Marathon\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2549}, {\"ngram\": \"the same route\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"the runners\", \"from\": 2619, \"to\": 2630}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The course for the marathon at the 2024 Olympics will take runners across a variety of landscapes and terrains, including three uphill stretches that actually are pretty steep.\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The course\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2679}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2696}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2717}, {\"ngram\": \"runners\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2735}, {\"ngram\": \"a variety\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2752}, {\"ngram\": \"landscapes\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2766}, {\"ngram\": \"terrains\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"three uphill stretches\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 2813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not anything they have not seen before, though the climbs are a bit longer than others they have endured.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2864}, {\"ngram\": \"the climbs\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2909}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will see a maximum gradient of 13.5%.\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 3000, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a maximum gradient\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2990}, {\"ngram\": \"13.5%\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 2999}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most notable climb will be a 600-meter challenge about 18 miles in that will see the athletes reach an average gradient of about 10.5%.\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The most notable climb\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3024}, {\"ngram\": \"a 600-meter challenge\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3054}, {\"ngram\": \"about 18 miles\", \"from\": 3055, \"to\": 3069}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"an average gradient\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3125}, {\"ngram\": \"about 10.5%\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In all, there will be more than 1,400 feet of elevation and, well, more than 1,400 feet of fast-paced descending.\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3256, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than 1,400 feet\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"elevation\", \"from\": 3189, \"to\": 3198}, {\"ngram\": \"well, more than 1,400 feet\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3230}, {\"ngram\": \"fast-paced descending\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Handling all of the ups and downs along the way will be key for the athletes as they prepare for the flatter run into the finish line.\", \"from\": 3257, \"to\": 3391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ups\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3280}, {\"ngram\": \"downs\", \"from\": 3285, \"to\": 3290}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3321, \"to\": 3333}, {\"ngram\": \"the flatter run\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3369}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both marathons at the 2024 Olympics will include past champions, world champions, record holders, winners of other major marathons, up-and-coming stars - you name it.\", \"from\": 3393, \"to\": 3559, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both marathons\", \"from\": 3393, \"to\": 3407}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympics\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3428}, {\"ngram\": \"past champions\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"world champions\", \"from\": 3458, \"to\": 3473}, {\"ngram\": \"record holders\", \"from\": 3475, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 3491, \"to\": 3498}, {\"ngram\": \"other major marathons\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3523}, {\"ngram\": \"up-and-coming stars\", \"from\": 3525, \"to\": 3544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the entrants on the men's side will be two-time defending Olympic champion Eliud Kipchoge of Kenya, who is one of seven men in history with more than one medal in the Olympic marathon and one of three with two golds.\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3642, \"end\": 3656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}, {\"begin\": 3660, \"end\": 3665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8767050184604154e-18, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the entrants\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3579}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's side\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3597}, {\"ngram\": \"seven men\", \"from\": 3681, \"to\": 3690}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3701}, {\"ngram\": \"more than one medal\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3726}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic marathon\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3750}, {\"ngram\": \"two golds\", \"from\": 3773, \"to\": 3782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kipchoge won the 2016 race in Rio de Janeiro in 2:08.44.\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3815, \"end\": 3829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7979476233258848e-23, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kipchoge\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3793}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 race\", \"from\": 3798, \"to\": 3811}, {\"ngram\": \"2:08.44\", \"from\": 3833, \"to\": 3840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He improved in Tokyo 2020, winning in 2:08.38.\", \"from\": 3842, \"to\": 3888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3857, \"end\": 3862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9984113847367853, \"rank\": 0.0015911429674891951, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2:08.38\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3887}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, he is 39 years old for this title defense.\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this title defense\", \"from\": 3918, \"to\": 3936}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Can he become the first man in history to win the event three consecutive times?\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4018, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first man\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 3965}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 3976}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 3984, \"to\": 3993}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other top contenders in Paris will be fellow Kenyan Benson Kipruto, Ethiopians Kenenisa Bekele and Tamirat Tola, Switzerland's Tadesse Abraham and Team USA's Connor Mantz and Clayton Young.\", \"from\": 4020, \"to\": 4209, \"entiti